The paper focuses on developing a planning approach for autonomous navigation and active perception in ambiguous and perceptually aliased environments. This involves reasoning about data association within belief evolution, which is a key aspect of robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the challenges of perceptual aliasing and the need to incorporate computer vision (cs.CV) techniques to handle this uncertainty. Additionally, the approach involves designing cost functions to measure uncertainty and ambiguity, which is related to control systems (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG).
